      "value": "What is a CDN?"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "value": "A Content Delivery Network (CDN) is a network of distributed servers that deliver website content to users based on their geographic location."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Why CDN Matters"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "value": "CDNs reduce latency, improve load speed, and provide better user experience by serving content from servers closer to the user."
